OL,3,CFather of terror attack victim says
OL,4,Chis son's death must not be in vain
OL,6,FThe father of a man who was murdered
OL,7,Fin a terror attack in Reading says the
OL,8,Fgovernment must not let his death be
OL,9,Fin vain.
OL,11,FGary Furlong's son James was stabbed
OL,12,Fto death by Khairi Saadallah in
OL,13,FForbury Gardens, along with Dr David
OL,14,FWails and Joseph Ritchie-Bennett, on
OL,15,FJune 20 2020.
OL,17,FHe has called for assurances from the
OL,18,FHome Secretary that changes will be
OL,19,Fproperly implemented.
