OL,3,CFather of terror attack victim says
OL,4,Chis son's death must not be in vain
OL,6,FHe said: "I have to keep pushing this
OL,7,Fprocess for James' legacy, in James'
OL,8,Fmemory that I do something to change
OL,9,Fthe future, that I do something to
OL,10,Fsave people's lives."
OL,12,FSaadallah was a failed asylum seeker
OL,13,Ffrom Libya and had a history of
OL,14,Fviolent behaviour.
OL,16,FHe was released from prison just two
OL,17,Fweeks before the attack.
OL,19,FHe is currently serving a whole-life
OL,20,Fsentence.
