OL,3,CFather of terror attack victim says
OL,4,Chis son's death must not be in vain
OL,6,FSpeaking in the House of Commons, Home
OL,7,FOffice Minister Dan Jarvis said he was
OL,8,Fhappy to meet the victims' families to
OL,9,Fdiscuss changes.
OL,11,FMr Jarvis said: "The Home Secretary
OL,12,Fand I are overseeing the
OL,13,Fimplementation of commitments made in
OL,14,Fresponse to the inquest and we are
OL,15,Fdetermined that all the lessons
OL,16,Flearned from this terrible incident
OL,17,Fare acted upon."
OL,19,FGary Furlong says "their actions will
OL,20,Fspeak louder than any words".
